main event: On 24 October 1957, northeast of Phillips, Wisconsin, a small round object the size of a basketball was observed, changing from red to white, and moving up and down in angles for 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as small, round, and changing color from red to white.
It moved up and down in angles, displaying unusual behavior.
The witness reported the observation lasting for 5 minutes, indicating a sustained sighting.
The document mentions the absence of photographs and insufficient data for analysis, leaving the event unexplained.
The witness was identified as a housewife, adding credibility to the report.
sighted object: small round object changing from red to white
